Pandas Data Structures

Three Data Structures:
Series: One-Dimensional labeled arrays pd.Series(data)
It is defined as a one-dimensional array that is capable of storing various data types.

import pandas as pd
s = pd.Series([10, 20, 30])
print(s)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
DataFrames: Two-Dimensional data structure with columns, table.
A DataFrame is the most important data structure in pandas. It represents tabular data arranged in rows and columns, similar to an Excel sheet or SQL table.

import pandas as pd

data = {
    "Name": ["Asad", "Ali", "Sara"],
    "Age": [25, 27, 24],
    "City": ["Delhi", "Mumbai", "Pune"]
}

df = pd.DataFrame(data)
print(df)
``
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Panel : A panel is a 3D container of data.
