## 1️⃣ Automatic Arithmetic (Column‑wise)

```python
import pandas as pd

df = pd.DataFrame({
    "Salary": [30000, 40000, 50000]
})

df["Bonus"] = df["Salary"] * 0.10
print(df)
```

✅ Bonus is calculated **automatically for every row**

***

## 2️⃣ Automatic Broadcasting (Single Value → All Rows)

```python
df["Tax_Rate"] = 5
```

✅ `5` is applied to **all rows automatically**

***

## 3️⃣ Automatic Conditional Operation

```python
df["High_Salary"] = df["Salary"] > 35000
print(df)
```

✅ Condition checked for **entire column at once**

***

## 4️⃣ Automatic Aggregation

```python
print(df["Salary"].sum())
print(df["Salary"].mean())
```

✅ No loop needed, pandas handles everything internally

***

## 5️⃣ Automatic Handling of Missing Values

```python
df = pd.DataFrame({
    "Marks": [80, 90, None, 70]
})

print(df["Marks"].mean())
```

✅ `NaN` is **ignored automatically**

***

## 6️⃣ Automatic String Operations

```python
df = pd.DataFrame({
    "Name": ["asad", "ali", "sara"]
})

df["Name"] = df["Name"].str.upper()
print(df)
```

✅ String function applied to **entire column**

***

## 7️⃣ Automatic Date Operations

```python
df = pd.DataFrame({
    "Date": pd.to_datetime(["2026-04-01", "2026-04-10"])
})

df["Day"] = df["Date"].dt.day
print(df)
```

✅ Dates processed column‑wise

***

## 8️⃣ Automatic GroupBy Operation

```python
df = pd.DataFrame({
    "Department": ["IT", "IT", "HR"],
    "Salary": [50000, 60000, 45000]
})

print(df.groupby("Department")["Salary"].mean())
```

✅ Pandas performs grouping + calculation automatically

***

## 9️⃣ Automatic Column Alignment

```python
df1 = pd.DataFrame({"A": [10, 20]})
df2 = pd.DataFrame({"A": [5, 5]})

print(df1 + df2)
```

✅ Columns are aligned by **name**, not position

