## ✅ Read CSV File in Pandas - > `read_csv()`

### Basic Syntax

```python
import pandas as pd

df = pd.read_csv("data.csv")
print(df)
```

```python
df = pd.read_csv("data.csv", sep=",", header=0, index_col=False)
```

| Parameter   | Purpose                         |
| ----------- | ------------------------------- |
| `sep`       | Column separator (`,` `;` `\t`) |
| `header`    | Row number for column names     |
| `index_col` | Column to use as index          |
| `usecols`   | Read selected columns           |
| `nrows`     | Read limited rows               |
| `skiprows`  | Skip rows                       |
| `dtype`     | Specify data types              |

### Example

```python
df = pd.read_csv("data.csv", usecols=["Name", "Age"], nrows=5)
```

