What is loc?

loc is a label‑based indexer used to select, update, insert, and modify data in a DataFrame using row labels and column names.

✅ Works with row labels + column names
✅ Supports conditions (filters)
✅ Can modify data directly
df.loc[row_label, column_label]
''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''
Select Rows + Specific Columns
df.loc[0:2, ["Name", "Age"]]
''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''''
#### Add a new row

```python
df.loc[len(df)] = ["Asad", 25, "IT"]
```
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
What is iloc?

iloc is a position‑based indexer used to select and modify DataFrame data using integer positions (row number & column number).

✅ Uses only integers
✅ Zero‑based indexing
✅ Works like Python list indexing
df.iloc[0:3]

